# theme for boxplots
theme_boxplot<- function () { 
  theme_classic(base_size=10, base_family="Helvetica") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size=10, color = "black"),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size=8, color="black"),
        axis.title.x= element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size=10, color="black"), 
        legend.position = "none")
}

#Here I am prepping the metaphlan2 data for read count adjustemnet
metaphlan <- read_tsv("/Volumes/turnbaughlab/qb3share/qiyanang/IDEO_manuscript_Rd2/data/merged_metaphlan2.tsv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_double(),
##   Taxonomy = col_character()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
metaphlan.taxonomy <- as_tibble(metaphlan$Taxonomy)
metaphlan$Taxonomy <- NULL
metaphlan <- metaphlan[,order(colnames(metaphlan))]

#Dividing by 100 to convert everything to fractions. All the percents sum to 1.0 (i.e. 100%)
metaphlan <- metaphlan/100

#These are read count data
read_count_adjustment <- read_tsv("/Volumes/turnbaughlab/qb3share/qiyanang/IDEO_manuscript_Rd2/data/merged_fastp.tsv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   Sample = col_character(),

#These are the processed read counts that include a variable where paired reads were used. We will use this for our adjustment
read_norm_adjustment <- read_tsv("/Volumes/turnbaughlab/qb3share/qiyanang/IDEO_manuscript_Rd2/data/merged_norm.tsv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   SampleID = col_character(),

##   ReadPairsPostQC = col_double(),
##   AverageGenomeSize = col_double(),
##   GenomeEquivalents = col_double()
## )
read_norm_adjustment <- read_norm_adjustment[order(read_norm_adjustment$SampleID),]
ReadPairsPostQC<-read_norm_adjustment$ReadPairsPostQC

metaphlancheck <- as_tibble(t(t(metaphlan) * ReadPairsPostQC))

#Here I am putting the taxonomy data back. I converted everything to tibbles.
metaphlan <- bind_cols(metaphlancheck, metaphlan.taxonomy) %>% rename("Taxonomy"="value")

metaphlan.species <- bind_cols(metaphlan.species.subsamp, metaphlan.species.taxonomy)
rownames(metaphlan.species) <- metaphlan.species$Taxonomy

metaphlan.aldex <- metaphlan.species[,1:45]

metaphlan.aldex <- metaphlan.aldex[,order(metadata$SampleID)]

conditions <- metadata$Ethnicity

ttests.species <- aldex(metaphlan.aldex, conditions = conditions, mc.samples=128, denom = "all", test = "t", effect = TRUE, include.sample.summary = TRUE)
## aldex.clr: generating Monte-Carlo instances and clr values
## operating in serial mode
## computing center with all features
## aldex.ttest: doing t-test
## aldex.effect: calculating effect sizes
ttests.species <- ttests.species %>% rownames_to_column("Species")
ttests.species$Phylum <- gsub("|c__.*.", "",ttests.species$Species)


ttests.species$Fold <- ttests.species$rab.win.Chinese/ttests.species$rab.win.White

ttests.species<-rename(ttests.species, "EA"="rab.win.Chinese", "W"="rab.win.White")

ttests.species$Phylum<-gsub("k__Bacteria|p__", "", ttests.species$Phylum)

ttests.species$Phylum<-gsub("k__Archaea", "", ttests.species$Phylum)

ttests.species$Phylum<-str_replace_all(ttests.species$Phylum,"[^[:alnum:]]", "")

eye <- ttests.species%>% filter(we.ep<0.05)

ttests.species$plotted.diff <-ttests.species$EA - ttests.species$W


ttests.species <- pivot_longer(ttests.species, cols = c("EA", "W"), names_to = "Ethnicity")
#InterestingPlot.long.variance<- pivot_longer(InterestingPlot, cols = c("WhiteVar", "ChineseVar"), names_to = "Ethnicity") %>% select(Taxonomy, value, Ethnicity) %>% rename("Variance"=value)
#InterestingPlot.long.variance$Ethnicity <- recode(InterestingPlot.long.variance$Ethnicity, WhiteVar="White", ChineseVar="Chinese")

#InterestingPlot.long <- left_join(InterestingPlot.long, InterestingPlot.long.variance, by=c("Taxonomy", "Ethnicity"))


ttests.species$Direction <- ifelse(ttests.species$plotted.diff>0, "Higher W", "Higher EA")

ttests.species$Alpha <- ifelse(ttests.species$we.ep < 0.05, 1, 0.75)

ttests.species$Line<-ifelse(ttests.species$we.ep < 0.05, "dashed","solid")

Down_Color="#440154FF"
Up_Color="#FDE725FF"

board <- ttests.species %>%
  filter(Phylum!="Euryarchaeota") %>%
  mutate(Phylum=factor(Phylum, levels=c("Firmicutes","Bacteroidetes","Actinobacteria","Proteobacteria","Verrucomicrobia"))) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Ethnicity, y=value, group=Species, fill=Ethnicity, alpha=Alpha)) +
  geom_point(shape=21, size=2, fill="grey", color="black") + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(W=Whitecolor, EA=Chinesecolor))+ 
  geom_line(aes(color=Direction, linetype=Line)) + 
  facet_wrap(~Phylum, nrow = 1) + 
  theme_MicrobeR() + 
  theme(strip.text = element_text(size=10,color="black"), axis.text.x = element_text(size=10,color="black"), axis.text.y = element_text(size=8,color="black"), axis.title = element_text(size=10, color="black")) +
  labs(color="Fold EA/W") + xlab("") +
  scale_alpha_continuous(range=c(0.3,1)) + 
  guides (alpha=FALSE) + ylab("Average abundance (CLR)") + 
  scale_color_manual(values=c("Higher EA"=Chinesecolor, "Higher W"=Whitecolor)) +
  theme(legend.position = "top")
board

colnames(eye)<-gsub("rab.sample.", "",colnames(eye))
facets <- eye %>% pivot_longer(contains("OB"), names_to="SampleID") %>% left_join(metadata)
## Joining, by = "SampleID"
facets$Ethnicity<-recode(facets$Ethnicity, "White"="W", "Chinese"="EA")
facets$Species<- str_extract(facets$Species, "\\b\\w+$")
facets$Species<-gsub("s__", "", facets$Species)
facets$Species<-gsub("_", " ", facets$Species)

side <- facets %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Ethnicity, y=value, fill=Ethnicity)) + 
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape=NA) + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(W=Whitecolor, EA=Chinesecolor)) + 
  facet_wrap(~Species, nrow = 2, scales = 'free') + 
  theme_MicrobeR() + 
  theme(strip.text = element_text(size=10,color="black"), axis.text = element_text(size=8,color="black")) +
  stat_compare_means(comparisons = list(c("EA", "W"))) + 
  theme(legend.position = "none") + 
  ylab("Abundance (CLR)") + xlab("")
side

# Plot combined figure
library(patchwork)
board + side + plot_layout(widths = c(2.5, 1))
